Imagemagick is a great software application if you have a little experience with
the command line.

### Example Commands
#### mogrify
    
    mogrify -resize 50% image.jpg

#### convert

    convert -resize 50% image.jpg image-2.jpg

### Shell Scripts
I use this shell script to automate imagemagick:

    #!/bin/sh
    mv $1 $2.jpg
    jpegoptim -f -m75 -o --strip-all $2.jpg
    exiftool -Copyright="Savonix Corporation" $2.jpg
    rm *nal
    convert -quality 70% -scale 50% $2.jpg $2.mini.jpg

This one too, though it doesn't use imagemagick:

    #!/bin/sh
    pngcrush -f -m75 -o --strip-all $1 $1_
    mv $1_ $1
    exiftool -Copyright="Savonix Corporation" $1
    rm *nal
    scp *.png 192.168.8.50:/var/www/public/s/img/2009/q1/
    echo "&lt;img src=\"/s/img/2009/q2/$1\"/>"

